    <div class="tested-box">
      <h3>How We Tested These Shilajit Gummies</h3>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Purchased independently.</strong> Every product was purchased at full retail price through Amazon or the brand's website. No brand sponsored this evaluation or was notified in advance.</li>
        <li><strong>Verified fulvic acid content.</strong> We cross-referenced label claims with third-party certificates of analysis. Products standardized to a specific fulvic acid percentage were prioritized over those listing only total shilajit weight.</li>
        <li><strong>Heavy metal screening.</strong> Shilajit naturally forms in mineral-rich geological deposits, creating inherent contamination risk. We evaluated each brand's heavy metal testing documentation for lead, arsenic, mercury, and cadmium levels.</li>
        <li><strong>Assessed source and processing.</strong> We reviewed geographic sourcing (Himalayan, Altai, Caucasus), purification methods (cold-processed vs. heat-extracted), and whether the brand disclosed its supply chain.</li>
        <li><strong>Evaluated clinical backing.</strong> Products using patented, clinically studied ingredients (PrimaVie) received higher evidence scores than generic shilajit extracts without published research support.</li>
        <li><strong>Taste and usability panel.</strong> Four team members evaluated each gummy on flavor, texture, aftertaste, and daily compliance. Shilajit's naturally mineral-heavy taste profile makes formulation quality a critical differentiator in gummy form.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <h2 id="who-should-take">Who Should Consider Shilajit Gummies?</h2>

    <p>Shilajit is most appropriate for adults seeking broad-spectrum mineral supplementation, natural testosterone support, or mitochondrial energy enhancement. Based on clinical evidence and our testing, these groups are most likely to benefit:</p>

    <div class="info-cards">
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Men over 40 seeking testosterone support</strong>
        <p>The 2016 Andrologia study specifically enrolled men aged 45-55 and demonstrated a 20% increase in total testosterone at 250mg/day over 90 days.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Athletes and active adults</strong>
        <p>Shilajit's CoQ10-boosting and mitochondrial support properties translate to improved exercise capacity, faster recovery, and reduced post-workout muscle damage markers.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Chronic fatigue and low energy</strong>
        <p>The fulvic acid and mineral complex addresses cellular energy production at the mitochondrial level — a fundamentally different mechanism than caffeine stimulation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Biohacking enthusiasts</strong>
        <p>Shilajit's mineral complexity and adaptogenic properties align with the biohacking community's focus on optimizing cellular function and longevity markers.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="warn-box">
      <span class="warn-box-ico">&#9888;</span>
      <p><strong>Who should NOT take shilajit:</strong> Pregnant or breastfeeding women — insufficient safety data. Individuals with hemochromatosis (iron overload disorder) — shilajit enhances iron absorption. People with gout — purines in shilajit may increase uric acid. Anyone with a known allergy to fulvic or humic acid compounds. If you take blood thinners or iron supplements, consult your physician before adding shilajit.</p>
    </div>

